records.addlTxt:
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of five (5) years.  That is two (2) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision.  Execution of sentence is stayed and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend four (4) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 04-05-16 by 5:00 p.m.;
2) Spend an additional eight (8) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
3) AODA assessment and follow through;
4) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) obtain GED within the first six months of probation;
9) maintain fulltime employment or work search;
10) no association with any known drug dealers or users;
11) complete one hundred (100) hours of community service.
The defendant has credit for two (2) days if revoked.
Minutes.
